The paper deals with clustering algorithms, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on pairwise similarity measures and the goal of putting similar objects in the same cluster suggests that the paper may also fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of optimization techniques and the study of worst-case error suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
